The paper discusses security issues in software-defined networks, which are related to computer networks (cs.NI) and security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a mechanism to protect authentication credentials and cryptographic context, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the performance impact of the proposed mechanism, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
